data.name: Label1.Text
data.value:
Double click a mod to move it in or out of the current preset. In the current preset, click and drag to reorder mods. (Note: this has no known effect in Arma)
To add/remove multiple mods, Ctrl or Shift click to select multiple items, then use the add/remove buttons.
Protip: By clicking the dropdown twice, you can use the scroll wheel to quickly scroll through your presets. (This works with all dropdowns in Windows)
Groups: Subgroups of mods can be managed using the Groups dialog. All the add/remove functionality of the main window works there as well. Hover over a group in the main window to quickly see the mods inside it.
What the list colors mean:

data.name: Label12.Text
data.value:
You can organize sub-modfolders in the Arma 3 directory, and the launcher will still find them, if the top folder starts with a @ symbol. For example, you can do "Arma 3\@Mods\@JSRS" and JSRS will show up in the launcher.
In "Options > Modfolder Locations...", you can specify additional folders to search for modfolders, even on other hard drives! You can have as many additional locations as you want, and you can enable and disable them at will.
Hover over a folder in the modfolder list to see its complete path.
